The article discusses the importance of the right to vote in a democracy and the recent efforts in Nevada to make voting easier. The Governor has signed into law legislation to increase access to the ballot box. The article emphasizes that when Americans vote, they not only choose their leaders but also shape the future of the nation and strengthen democracy. The Biden-Harris Administration supports the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act, which aim to ensure fair participation in every state and address racial discrimination in elections.